									<td bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td class="subjectbar"  style="font-size: 10pt;padding-left:10px;" width="100%">
									Bards & EQ.  My assesment.
																	</td>
							<td class="subjectbar" align=right style="padding:0px;padding-right:10px;">		
		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 
		id="individual_options_3369_table" 
		onClick="setId('3369');show(this,'individual_options_3369','right',false);" 
		onDblClick="setId('3369');show(this,'individual_options_3369','right',false);" 
	 >
	<tr class=clickable>
					<td nowrap><a class=subjectbar style='font-size: 8pt;'>Options</a></td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
		<td><img src='/i/skins/default/button_options.gif' border=0 alt='' width=11 height=28></td>
		<td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
	</table>
	
	
</td></tr>
						
		<tr>
			
			<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>

						
							
				
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=1080' class="auth_text" style="font-weight:bold;"><span style='color:#4D7AB0;'>Tremelo-1018-Prexus</span></a>
				<br>

								
				<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
									Hero
								<br>
									Posts: 792<br>
													Registered: 03-01-2004
				
				</span>
									<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
								
				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=1080'>			
	
			<img src="http://home.comcast.net/~jgupta/Tremelo.jpg" border=0 alt="">
		</a><br>

				<span class=text_smallest>
								Server: Prexus<br>
								</span>

								
			
			
									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 252 times<br>
									</span>

												</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify;  background-color: #020A0F;   background-image: none;  background-repeat: repeat-x; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Bards overall are not that bad off.&nbsp; Relatively speaking, there's no class that's really bad off.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Bards specifically are feeling the crunch of being left behind.&nbsp; The golden age of barding was during PoP.&nbsp; We got AAs and songs that (mostly) made sense.&nbsp; I say mostly becuase at this time a very disturbing trend began to take shape with bards and the songs they were given.&nbsp; This trend was to supply upgrades to songs like casters.&nbsp; Bards aren't casters.&nbsp; Our songs are supposed to last forever (or a very long period of time).&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We're not supposed to get 3 versions of mez in 1 expansion.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Even with all that, we were only percieved as powerful becuase we were desired in groups and raids.&nbsp; No ability alone made us powerful.&nbsp; In other words, we weren't doing amazing things, we were just making our parties feel like they were much more powerful.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's the "grass is greener" syndrome.&nbsp; Everyone desires the buffs that a bard brings to a group, therefore bards are an uber powerful class.&nbsp; Our dps contribution is laughable and every group I've been in, the casters still demanded having KEI and all the melee classes demanded having VoQ.&nbsp; Still, it was enough for us to be an enhancer (but usually never the primary) buffer of the group.&nbsp; Fortunately most zones were outdoors which allowed us to be pullers, becuase of selos and not becuase of fade.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In LoY, LDoN, GoD &amp; OoW bards really got very little in terms of song upgrades.&nbsp; Most were rehashes of useless songs or linear upgrades or (to some extent) downgrades to songs we already had.&nbsp; Bards really felt (and still are feeling) the cruch of being percieved as an uber class.&nbsp; IMO, no AA or songs were really well thought out.&nbsp; They all seemed to be a last minute addition with (if we were lucky) a linear interpolation of what we already had.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's sad becuase all the bard boards have incredibly amazing suggestions on what abilities could be added to bards.&nbsp; Almost nothing had to be designed, all that had to be done was to read the boards and (evaluate and) implement the suggestions.&nbsp; Instead, we bought an expansion(s) that added nothing new.&nbsp; There are huge difference between a Kunark, Velious and PoP bard.&nbsp; But a PoP bard and a OoW bard are almost identical.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm betting that's true for all classes and that's one of the reasons why all classes are unhappy with what they have.&nbsp; There's been nothing new and exciting for us in years.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But that's not the only reason why most people are unhappy.&nbsp; I think I can sum it up in one sentance:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I feel weak.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is a general problem with EQ and not just with the bard class.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think I felt the strongest when I was a level 3 bard fighting bats and skeletons in gfay.&nbsp; I felt that I had accomplished a significant goal (leveling to 3).&nbsp; I was not afraid of bats or skeletons and felt control over my situation.&nbsp; Yes, there was the level 4 orc pawn in the distance, but, in my imediate domain, I was the master.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now, I'm an uber level 70 bard with all GoD, Time and (pre-anguish) OoW equipment one of the top 50 bards serverwide (pre-WoW and EQ2).&nbsp; I'm one of the uberest characters on my server.&nbsp; I have close to 600AAs.&nbsp; Yet, when I encounter a level 62 mob I run away like a little school girl and then bring back 5 of my uber buddies to go beat up this lowely common runt.&nbsp; Even then, this pathetic creature can wipe my group if something goes wrong.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I can't begin to imagine how non-raiding characters with bazaar bought equipment with 1/4 of my DPS, AC &amp; HP feel when they run into these mobs.&nbsp; What sense of acomplishment have they reached?&nbsp; What do they have to look forward too knowing if they become uber, the only real advantage over that one mob is that they can take more hits from behind while they run to the zone line with thier tails between thier legs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Everyone is complaining about their DPS (or lack there of) becuase they feel weak.&nbsp; All classes are balanced relative to themselves, but, we are pathetic against mobs.&nbsp; We seek out any advantage that we can to justify our being in EQ.&nbsp;&nbsp; We try to gain a few percentage points here and there but in the end it really makes no difference what so ever.&nbsp; The best DPS classes want more utility to be desired.&nbsp; The best utility classes want more DPS to be desired.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What everyone really desires is the feeling of uberness and no one is getting it.&nbsp; Not the hardcore raider, not the hardcore non-raider, not the casual player and nobody in between.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Here's what it should be like to be a any level 70 character (full hp, full mana) in EQ:<BR>You encounter a common mob up to level 70.&nbsp; You fight it, take hits, but in the end you have a very good chance to beat it.&nbsp;&nbsp; If you're an uber character, you can take on 2 of these common level 70 mobs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Groups shouldn't be single pulling mobs.&nbsp; A level 70 group pulls a level 65 mobs and then gang beats the snot out of them.&nbsp; How uber is that?&nbsp; Level 70 groups should be pulling 6 (level 70) mobs at a time and killing 6 mobs at a time.&nbsp; There's 6 people in a group, they should be killing 6 mobs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There should be a motivation for multipulling... such as a gang kill bonus.&nbsp; If you have 6 mobs engaged, the first mob is woth 160% (plus group and zone) xp.&nbsp; 5 mobs = 150%... 1 mob = 100%.&nbsp; Groups of mobs should be linked so by default they come in gangs.&nbsp; But, should still have the aspect of being split.&nbsp; In other words a gang of 9 mobs exists, but in general only 3 will agro.&nbsp; Groups can still split mobs if they need to (down to singles) but don't get the extra bonus.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mob's HP should be much lower (player DPS shouldn't increase), along with the base xp and respawn timers, so that mass slayings is the common goal of level 70 characters.&nbsp; Currently, trash mob HP is just way too high.&nbsp; It doesn't matter if I do 200 DPS or 300 DPS.&nbsp; It's relatively a small difference vs how many damage I have to do.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Of course, there needs to be those unique mobs that have massively great HP and AC (named &amp; raid mobs), but the common stuff doesnt need to be more uber than the average player.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Bards are OK but havent gotton anything new for a while.&nbsp; All classes are (mostly) balanced relative to each other, but they are not balanced against the eviornment.&nbsp; Give all classes the ability to feel good about themselves.&nbsp; Nerf trash mobs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Anyways, that's my opinion of Bards, EQ and how to make it fun again.&nbsp; Feel free to disagree becuase we all have our own opinions of how things should be.</DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
														<p>- <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22184">Tremelo</a> <br>Proud member of Unity on Prexus
							</div>
																
