			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<P>Kulamiena, that isn't what Trem said.&nbsp; He said that the various classes are more or less balanced against each other.</P>
<P>He said bards (and all classes in general) need improvements in 1) new abilities, 2) more power versus the environment, and 3) soloability.&nbsp; He mentioned that even as a power-house of a bard, it takes a group of people to gank a single mob that is almost 10 levels lower than them.&nbsp; </P>
<P>This describes a class that needs improvements, not a class that is fine.&nbsp; Re-read the post.&nbsp; He is calling for improvements, they just don't included the "SOE suxors" comments that usually come along with pleads for improvement</P>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
														<p>Jarroll Lonelysong - The Commune<br><br>Bard of Xegony<br><br>/join xegony.bards:bards<br>
							</div>
																
