												<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Kulamiena wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Rereading the post will not change the fact that Trem apparently believes that bards are balanced as compared to other classes. That is what SOE means when they talk about balance, not some nebulous 'vs the game' balance. </DIV>
<DIV>The /con system is broken. That, apparently, is the only problem with bards (AND all other classes) according to the person who has been our advocate these many months.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Kula</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>You may believe that bards are broken and are an unplayable class.&nbsp; I claim they are a very playable class&nbsp;who are highly desired in groups and raids.&nbsp; They&nbsp;can also solo (reguardless of how boring) with no down time.&nbsp;</P>
<P>You may think they are not balanced.&nbsp; I say go look at the top 10 list.&nbsp; Just look at the top 5 most important things to bards: 1 &amp; 5&nbsp;is a system wide mobs are too uber vs players. 2 is an annoyance fix. 3 &amp; 4&nbsp;are balance issues.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Of the balance issues, the modifier cap is looking for scraps.&nbsp; It's a pathetic upgrade even if it is to go live and there are only 2 instances where it would have any effect: AE resists would increase by less than 10 points and DoT damage would increase by 5%.&nbsp; In almost every other situation, no one is equiping instruments and it wont make any difference... the bards who have 3.4+ drums also have access to equipment that has modifiers on it.&nbsp; The reason why it's an issue is becuase it's an insult to bards.</P>
<P>The ability to hold agro is the only real bard balance issue we have in the first 5 slots.&nbsp;I wont go into detail about how I feel reguarding this issue, but I can say that I have been MT for quite a few groups in MPG.</P>
<P>Ask any other class if they think bards are balanced.&nbsp; Ask them if they think bards are overpowered.&nbsp; Sometimes, you just gotta step back and take a look at the whole picture.&nbsp; I stand by my opinion that all classes are pretty well balanced in reguards to each other.&nbsp; That doesn't mean there's not specific problems with individual classes that require attention.</P>
<P>If you're not willing to look at other classes issues and concerns, you really have no understanding of what class balance&nbsp;&nbsp;is.</P>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
														<p>- <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22184">Tremelo</a> <br>Proud member of Unity on Prexus
