						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>I don't think bards are unplayable. I think we're balanced as far as groups go when we pull. But, yes I do think we are lacking in what we bring to raids beyond the first 2 bards. As you add that 3rd bard you now have to look at what that bard brings to the raid that another pure class doesn't do better. The answer: nothing. We still don't stack well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would also say that with the advent of the shaman over-buffs in OoW and the inflation of stats on gear since PoP we have been somewhat reduced in effectiveness in groups as less of our buffs have any effect on the group's power. As well, the minimal increase in mana provided by the OoW songs compares less than favorably with the increases available through FT and buff mana regens. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Prior to GoD a bard could fill the 6th slot in a group and compare favorably to that 6th slot going to a 'pure' DPS class because of the boost in group strength. When we stopped being able to do that we became just another pull class. Better in some spots, equal in most, worse in others. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>When was the last time you were invited to a group as a power member as opposed to puller? Groups used to complain that they lost bardbuffs during pulls. Today it's a non-issue. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What exactly am I not seeing?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Kula</DIV>
