									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 36 times<br>
									</span>

									
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>I agree with a lot of the stuff mentioned, and disaree with a little of it, which is fine.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Upon thinking about both posts I came to the conclusion that both sides are right, and both sides are wrong.&nbsp; GoD and OoW brought a lot of new mobs to the player base, mobs that were a lot harder to kill than previous mobs, so balances had to be introduced to offset it.&nbsp; GoD and OoW are actual one expansion, just split up.&nbsp; Where is the new, bold idea?&nbsp; SOE never implimented it.&nbsp; Most groups are comprised of a tank class, a healer class, crowd control class, melee dps class, caster dps class, and puller.&nbsp; With 15 classes plus (too lazy to try and count them all now) classes have been watered down into certain roles within this framework.&nbsp; It's the watering down that is stagnating the game, the classes, the experience, the creativity, and the fun.&nbsp; The framework was outgrown in GoD, but was never upgraded.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>GoD introduced the new Guild Management UI, and OoW continued it with additional features.&nbsp; What new features outside of leadership has been added to groups?&nbsp; I could group with five other players back in the very beginning of Everquest.&nbsp; There was a lot more variety of class abilities then, and a lot less classes to chose from, so there was a lot more room for experimentation and creativity.&nbsp; Kunark introduced the Holy Trinity.&nbsp; Vellious expanded it to a Holy Trinity of Four.&nbsp; Creativy and experimentation pretty much died there, but had a few resurgences here and there, but the damage was done.&nbsp; Look at high end raids?&nbsp; Just a single example: pulling.&nbsp; There cad be a wide cariety of classes pulling at a raid.&nbsp; Look at healing, again, a wide variety of classes participate.&nbsp; The same can be said for every class function, except one: lock picking, which is solely the rogue class.&nbsp; Why?&nbsp; Because rogues have to be the only class with the ability?&nbsp; Why?&nbsp; Doesn't that promote the stagnation?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>SOE didn't implement new group functionality.&nbsp; Power increases, mob hitpoints, and everything else&nbsp; went up, but the frameworked group power has decreased in comparison, stagnating within the rigidity of the Holy Trinity of the group.&nbsp; Increase the group slots like the buff slots and casting gems.&nbsp; A broader, larger &nbsp;Holy Trinity Group Framework can allow for more creativity, experimentation, and variety in roles.&nbsp; This is the logical enhancement for the group, an enhancement that didn't happen.&nbsp; A new Holy Trinity Group Framework can allow for more varied roles of each class.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Lowering the mob hps isn't the answer.&nbsp; This would result in feeding farm fests like those of LDoN.&nbsp; Instead of doing hard LDoNs at level 65, it was zerg festing normals.&nbsp; Very little risk at all.&nbsp; Increasing the character dps to match the mobs doesn't work either, for the same reasons.&nbsp; So, the only thing left is to increase the group.&nbsp; However, the only way to increase the group without increasing the character is by increasing the number of characters that comprise a group.&nbsp; How many?&nbsp; No idea.&nbsp; I'll let SOE debate the issue.&nbsp; I will say this much, the number of group members needs to balanced to the number of classes in the game, allowing for specialization, but at the same time for variety.&nbsp; In so doing all classes can have a specialization, but also a weakness, forever making it a balancing act for the perfect group, with environments consisting of like variety and specialization.&nbsp; All classes could bring something unique, and special, but with built in risks, just like the environment they are in, but with loot itemization also specialized and varied. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Polara</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
		<tr>

